    <briefdescription>
<para>A block of <ref refid="structDali_1_1SignalConnectionNode" kindref="compound">SignalConnectionNode</ref> slots in a chained-block pool. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Blocks are allocated as contiguous memory: the block header followed by an array of <ref refid="classDali_1_1SignalConnection" kindref="compound">SignalConnection</ref> slots. Blocks are chained in allocation order and never move once allocated, so pointers to slots are stable for the lifetime of the pool.</para>
<para>@SINCE_2_5.17 </para>
    </detaileddescription>
